incident_updates.body:
We will be performing routine maintenance on our Web Backend. Please refer to https://support.zoom.us/hc/en-us/articles/204758419 for more details. This update includes an SSO certificate rotation.

There is no operational impact. All services will be available during this scheduled update.

We will be performing maintenance on our Denver data center on December 10th, 2022.

No new meetings will be started in the Denver data center after 12:00AM MT (11PM Pacific Time/2AM Eastern Time) on December 10th. However, if any meetings started in the Denver data center are still ongoing at 12:00AM MT (11PM Pacific Time/2AM Eastern Time) on December 10th, they will be ended and can be manually restarted in a different data center.

If you obtain Zoom through one of our carrier partners leveraging Telephony Service Provider (TSP) integration, no new TSP connections will be started in the DV data center after 12:00AM MT (11PM Pacific Time/2AM Eastern Time) on December 10th. However, at 12:00AM MT (11PM Pacific Time/2AM Eastern Time) on December 10th, any TSP connections started in the DV data center that have been running for over 12 hours will be ended and can be manually restarted in a different data center.

Zoom Phone users registered to the Denver data center will be automatically registered in an alternative datacenter starting at 6:00AM Mountain Time (5:00AM Pacific/8:00AM Eastern) on December 10th. During the maintenance window, a brief disconnection may be experienced and notifications may be missed. If you get disconnected, the system will attempt to reconnect you automatically. If you are a BYOC (Bring Your Own Carrier) customer, please ensure that your Session Border Controller (SBC) is configured with alternate routing to Zoom’s San Jose data center in addition to the Denver data center. During the maintenance window, connectivity to Zoom’s Denver data center will be blocked which will force calls from the Session Border Controller (SBC) to failover to Zoom’s San Jose data center. Traffic will continue to be routed through the Zoom Denver data center once the maintenance is completed.

scheduled_maintenances.name: Scheduled Zoom Software Quarterly Lifecycle update (2/4/23)

incident_updates.body:
Zoom will be enforcing a new minimum version of all our Zoom clients and plugins, roughly 90 days from now on February 4th, 2023. This affects the following products: 
- Zoom client for meetings (Windows, macOS, Linux, iOS, Android, Blackberry, and Intune)
- Zoom Rooms (including Zoom Room Controllers) 
- Zoom Phone Appliances
- VDI Client and Plugin
- Virtual Room Connector
- Meetings Connector
- Recording Connector
- Meetings SDK (Native and Web)
- Video SDK (Native and Web)

Please ensure your devices are updated to the latest version. 

For more information, such as specific versions we are enforcing, please see the Zoom Software Quarterly Lifecycle Policy support article: https://support.zoom.us/hc/en-us/articles/360059429231 

To assist with checking the client versions on your account, refer to the Dashboard support article for more information: https://support.zoom.us/hc/en-us/articles/360039656511#h_13ce9a73-91e5-4df6-9cb5-c815b1605cf5
